data.rationale:
The NESSIE winner for 128-bit key, 64-bit block cipher. Misty1 is
    the first block cipher that is provably secure against linear and
    differential cryptanalysis. A variant of Misty1, dubbed as KASUMI
    (Japanese for "misty") is now the mandatory cipher in W-CDMA.
